            <h1 class="title text-center">Fluffy pancakes with coconut</h1>
            <hr>
            <div class="row">
                <div class="col mx-2 mb-3">
                    <h3>Ingredients</h3>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>40 gr</strong> oats</li>
                        <li><strong>30 gr</strong> grated dried coconut</li>
                        <li><strong>60 ml</strong> milk (any of your choice)</li>
                        <li><strong>2 teaspoons</strong> baking powder</li>
                        <li><strong>2</strong> eggs</li>
                        <li><strong>2 tablespoons</strong> flour</li>
                        <li><strong>1/4 teaspoon</strong> salt</li>
                    </ul>
                    <h4>Toppings</h4>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>2 tablespoons</strong> honey</li>
                        <li><strong>6 tablespoons</strong> forest fruits (frozen or not)</li>
                    </ul>
                    <h3>Directions</h3>
                    <ol>
                        <li>Put all the ingredients in the multi and beat for 1 minute.</li>
                        <li>Put a little fat in a non-stick pan and clean with a paper towel.</li>
                        <li>Put the pan on high heat and as soon as it heats up, take the mixture with 1 tablespoon and place it carefully. Cover the pan with a large lid and lower the heat to medium.</li>
                        <li>Leave each side of the pancake for 1 minute and remove.</li>
                        <li>For the toppings, put the honey and the fruit in a pan on a low heat. Leave for 2 minutes until they soften.</li>
                        <li>Place on top of the pancakes and add a little coconut at the end.</li>
                    </ol>
